Name: vulvovaginal candidiasis
Definition: A candidiasis that involves fungal infection of the vaginal mucous membranes in women caused by Candida albicans. The symptoms include intense vulval pruritus

Name: neonatal candidiasis
Definition: A candidiasis that involves fungal infection in neonates caused by Candida species. Low birthweight and age

Name: obsolete Pseudomonas septicemia
Definition: A candidiasis that involves fungal infection in neonates caused by Candida species. Low birthweight and age
